From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000012 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jason Gross <jason@theorem.dev>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 07:45:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm: init_putv must store long double constants, not skip them

Companion to patch 0011 (which fixed the VT_FLOAT/VT_DOUBLE bootstrap
arms). init_putv()'s `case VT_LDOUBLE` has, under `#if BOOTSTRAP &&
__arm__` (present in the mes-0.27 base fork, not added by this series),
an EMPTY stub:

    case VT_LDOUBLE:
        if (sizeof(long double) == LDOUBLE_SIZE)
    #if !(BOOTSTRAP && __arm__)
            *(long double *)ptr = vtop->c.ld;
    #else
        {
          // XXX TODO: breaks on mescc/tcc-mes based build
        }
    #endif
        else if (sizeof(double) == LDOUBLE_SIZE)
            *(double *)ptr = (double)vtop->c.ld;
        ...

On ARM EABI `long double == double == 8 bytes`, so `LDOUBLE_SIZE` is 8
(arm-gen.c) and `sizeof(long double) == LDOUBLE_SIZE` is true: control
enters the empty branch and never reaches the working
`else if (sizeof(double) == LDOUBLE_SIZE)` fallback. The `.data` slot,
already zero-filled by section_reserve(), is left untouched -- so every
long double constant a bootstrap arm tcc materializes lands as 0.0.

This is invisible to the self-host fixpoint (tcc.c materializes no long
double constants) but corrupts long-double-heavy code compiled by the
bootstrap tcc. Concretely it zeros musl __floatscan's
`1000000000.0L` digit-assembly constant (floatscan.c:262), which is one
of several defects that break the from-seed tcc's decimal FP handling.

Fix it the same way patch 0011 fixes VT_DOUBLE: bit-copy the two words
through the CValue union's integer view (`tab[]`, which aliases `ld` and
is int[LDOUBLE_SIZE/4] = int[2] here). No FP store, no conversion, only
idioms MesCC already compiles. A gcc build is unaffected (it never takes
the bootstrap arm).

NOTE: this patch is necessary but not by itself sufficient to make the
from-seed arm tcc parse fractional FP literals correctly -- the decimal
strtod / hex-float `ldexp` paths carry a separate, deeper defect (MesCC
compiles all floating point as 32-bit integer, so mes libc's ldexp stub
and strtod backend cannot work under it; reported separately). It is
included as a genuine, independently-correct bug fix.
---
 tccgen.c | 13 ++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tccgen.c b/tccgen.c
index ba26b7d..ffc863b 100644
--- a/tccgen.c
+++ b/tccgen.c
@@ -6402,11 +6402,14 @@ static void init_putv(CType *type, Section *sec, unsigned long c)
 		    *(long double *)ptr = vtop->c.ld;
 #else
                 {
-                  // XXX TODO: breaks on mescc/tcc-mes based build
-                  // maybe disable with HAVE_LONG_DOUBLE?
-                  //struct long_double *ldptr = ptr;
-                  //struct long_double tmp = (struct long_double)vtop->c.ld;
-                  //*ldptr = (struct long_double)tmp;
+                  /* long double == double (8 bytes) on ARM EABI, so
+                     LDOUBLE_SIZE==8 and c.tab[] (int[LDOUBLE_SIZE/4]) holds
+                     the full IEEE representation. Bit-copy via the union's
+                     int view, as patch 0011 does for VT_DOUBLE; the old empty
+                     stub left every long double constant as 0.0. */
+                  unsigned *uptr = ptr;
+                  uptr[0] = vtop->c.tab[0];
+                  uptr[1] = vtop->c.tab[1];
                 }
 #endif
 		else if (sizeof(double) == LDOUBLE_SIZE)
